                            <comment id="17413" author="jdb" created="Thu, 27 Apr 2006 13:09:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think it would be best to override both cause and rootCause:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;public class NestedServletException extends ServletException {&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;private Throwable cause = this;&lt;br/&gt;
private Throwable rootCause;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;public synchronized Throwable initCause(Throwable cause) {&lt;br/&gt;
    if (this.cause != this)&lt;br/&gt;
        throw new IllegalStateException(&quot;Can&apos;t overwrite cause&quot;);&lt;br/&gt;
    if (cause == this)&lt;br/&gt;
        throw new IllegalArgumentException(&quot;Self-causation not permitted&quot;);&lt;br/&gt;
    this.cause = cause;&lt;br/&gt;
    return this;&lt;br/&gt;
}&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;public Throwable getCause() {&lt;br/&gt;
    return (cause == this ? rootCause : cause);&lt;br/&gt;
}&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;public Throwable getRootCause() {&lt;br/&gt;
    return rootCause;&lt;br/&gt;
}&lt;br/&gt;
}&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17508" author="juergen.hoeller" created="Sat, 6 May 2006 08:00:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for pointing this out! Indeed, newer ServletException implementations might delegate from getRootCause to getCause themselves... which we didn&apos;t expect. The only reason why we override getCause there is to add JDK 1.4 compliance to the standard ServletException class. I guess this is rather futile, hence I&apos;ve dropped this method and simply let getMessage etc access the standard getRootCause method. After all, the only reason of existence for NestedServletException is better handling of the root cause in messages and stack traces.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Juergen&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
